Package: rtui
Title: R Bindings for Textual Terminal User Interfaces
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Arijit Ghosh", , , "arijitghosh2009@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Idiomatic R bindings to Python's Textual framework, enabling R
    users to author full-screen terminal user interfaces (TUIs) with panels,
    focus management, event loops, and CSS-like styling without writing Python.
    Uses 'reticulate' to bridge R and Python in a single process.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.3.3
Imports:
    reticulate (>= 1.35),
    R6,
    rlang,
    cli
Suggests:
